edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.filter

Class DimensionSwappingFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.filter.Filter
      • edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.filter.DimensionSwappingFilter

  • public class DimensionSwappingFilter
extends Filter
    A filter that wraps a DimensionFlipper and swaps two of the dimensions in an image.

    The two dimensions to be swapped can be specified using the setDimensionsToSwap(int, int) method, or by setting the parameters first_dimension_to_swap and second_dimension_to_swap as integer parameters. In either case, the dimensions to be swapped should be specified according to the dimension constants in ImageCoordinate. Specifying the dimensions in the parameter file will override the setting using setDimensionsToSwap(int, int).

    The argument to the apply method should be the Image whose dimensions will be swapped. (In contrast to the DimensionFlipper, this Image will be modified in place.)

    This filter does not use a reference Image.

    Author:
    Colin J. Fuller

      • setDimensionsToSwap

        public void setDimensionsToSwap(int dim0,
                       int dim1)
        Sets the two dimensions to swap in the image. These should correspond to the dimension constants defined in ImageCoordinate (or, rarely, to a user-defined dimension).

        These will override any dimensions specified in the parameter file.

        Parameters:
        dim0 - The first dimension to swap.
        dim1 - The second dimension to swap.
